  "text": "where y is an n × 1 response vector, ε ∼ N n (0, σ 2 I), X j is an n × K j matrix corresponding to the jth group, K j is the number of elements in group j, and β j is the associated K j × 1 coefficient vector. In equation [CITATION_1] , we take y to be centered, thereby eliminating the need for an intercept. To perform variable selection at the group level, Yuan and Lin 2 proposed the group lasso estimator, defined as the value β minimizing ",
